                    <msContents>
                        <summary>The <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_1167">Jāmiʻ-i ʻAbbāsī</title> A popular compendium on Islamic law commenced by the leading Twelver Shi‘a theologian of Iran at the time, <persName
                            key="person_27052262" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/27052262/"
                            type="standard" role="aut" change="#role-assignment">Muḥammad
                            ʻĀmilī (1547–1621)</persName>at the behest of his patron, Safavid ruler <persName ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/77109363/" key="person_77109363" xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard" role="pat"
                                change="#role-assignment">ʻAbbās I (b. 1571, r. 1588–1629)
                                ‎</persName>. However, at the time of his death he had only completed the first five chapters, to which his student <persName key="person_296725355" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/296725355"
                                role="ctb" change="#role-assignment">Niẓām ibn Ḥusayn
                                    Ṣāvajī (fl. 17th c)</persName> fifteen added another posthumously, as explained in the preface to Chapter 6. A brief list of contents for all 20 chapters (<hi rend="italic">bāb</hi>) appears at the end of the first preface.</summary>
                        <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_751-item1">
                            <author key="person_27052262" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/27052262/">
                                <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">ʻĀmilī, Bahāʼ al-Dīn Muḥammad ibn
                                    Ḥusayn, 1547–1621</persName>
                                <persName xml:lang="ar" 
                                    >العاملي، بهاء الدين محمد بن حسين</persName>
                            </author>
                            <author key="person_296725355" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/296725355"
                                role="ctb wst">
                                <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc">Ṣāvajī, Niẓām ibn Ḥusayn
                                     (fl. 17th c)</persName>; <lb/>
                                <persName xml:lang="ar" role="aut" 
                                    >نظام بن حسين صاوجى</persName>
                            </author>
                            <editor ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/77109363/" key="person_77109363" role="pat dte">
                                <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard" role="pat"
                                        change="#role-assignment">ʻAbbās I, Shah of Iran, b. 1571, r. 1588–1629
                                        ‎</persName>; <lb/>
                                    <persName xml:lang="fa" role="pat" change="#role-assignment">شاه
                                        عباس اول</persName>
                            </editor>
                            <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_1167">Jāmiʻ-i ʻAbbāsī</title>
                            <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_1167">جامع عباسي</title>
                            <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_751-item1-item1">
                                <locus from="1b" to="1b">Folio 1b</locus>
                                <title xml:lang="en">Preface</title>
                                <title xml:lang="fa">ديباچه</title>
                            <incipit xml:lang="fa" type="basmala"><locus from="1b" to="1b"> برگ ۱پ
                                    (folio 1b):</locus> الحمد لله رب العالمین و الصلوه علی اشرف
                                الاولین و الاخرین محمد سید المرسلین و علی بن ابی طالب امومنین و افضل
                                الوصین و اولادهما الائمه الطاهرین صلواه الله و سلامه علیهم اجمعین
                                اما بعد جون توجه خاطر ملکوت ناظر اشرف اقدس کلب آستان علی بن ابی طالب
                                علیه السلام شاه عباس الحسنی الموسوی الصفوی بهادر خان که اسم اشرفش از
                                بینات خلد الله ملکه هویدا و ظاهر است بانتشار مسائل دینی و اشتهار از
                                بینات خلد الله ملکه هویدا و ظاهر است بانتشار مسائل دینی و اشتهار
                                معارف یقینی مصروف و معطوفست... </incipit>
                            </msItem>
